The paper discusses the use of altmetrics to assess the societal impact of research, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the management and analysis of digital information, including scholarly publications. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) are also relevant as they deal with the social impact of technology. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as it deals with the analysis of information sources, including scholarly publications. cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also relevant as it deals with the study of social phenomena.
